[Patient] What can I eat to help manage my heart failure?
[Educator] Focus on fruits, veggies, whole grains, and lean proteins like chicken or fish.
[Patient] I can't afford expensive food, what are some budget-friendly options?
[Educator] Look into local food banks, community gardens, and farmers' markets for affordable options.
[Patient] I live in an unsafe neighborhood, how can I access healthy food?
[Educator] Check if there are food delivery services or transportation options available in your area.
[Patient] My culture has specific foods, how can I make them heart-healthy?
[Educator] Try adapting traditional recipes with healthier ingredients like using whole grains or lean meats.
[Patient] Are there any resources to help me with meal planning?
[Educator] Look for online resources or apps that provide meal planning tips and heart-healthy recipes.
[Patient] How can I make sure I'm getting enough nutrients on a tight budget?
[Educator] Focus on buying nutrient-dense foods like beans, lentils, and frozen fruits and veggies.
[Patient] What should I avoid eating to help manage my heart failure?
[Educator] Limit foods high in sodium, saturated fats, and added sugars like processed foods and sugary drinks.
[Patient] Can you recommend any specific heart-healthy recipes for me to try?
[Educator] How about trying a veggie stir-fry with brown rice or a grilled chicken salad with lots of veggies?